Subject: gen-dynapi/dynapi: MTEXT rect_width DXF code is 41, not 40

dynapi.c gave both MTEXT rect_width and text_height DXF code 40, so the DXF
importer put the char height (group 40) into rect_width and left
text_height 0. A zero text height makes AutoCAD/BricsCAD render the MTEXT
at a huge fallback size (the "giant magenta text" on re-saved drawings).

Root cause in gen-dynapi.pl: the field->dxf map is keyed per entity by
field name, so MTEXT's redundant re-read of rect_width in the annotative
context (dwg.spec: FIELD_BD (rect_width, 40) in the "redundant fields"
block) clobbered the canonical FIELD_BD (rect_width, 41). Keep the FIRST
dxf code for a field. Regenerated dynapi.c then gives rect_width 41.

Verified: MTEXT now decodes byte-identical to ODA's ACAD2000 output.

Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

--- a/src/gen-dynapi.pl
+++ b/src/gen-dynapi.pl
@@ -460,7 +460,12 @@
             }
 
-            # (scale.x, 41) as is
-            $DXF{$n}->{$f} = $dxf  if $dxf;
+            # (scale.x, 41) as is.
+            # Keep the FIRST dxf code for a field: some entities re-read a
+            # field in a later (embedded/redundant) context with a different
+            # group code (e.g. MTEXT rect_width is 41 in the primary object
+            # but re-appears as 40 in the annotative context), which used to
+            # clobber the canonical mapping and mis-import the field.
+            $DXF{$n}->{$f} = $dxf  if $dxf and !exists $DXF{$n}->{$f};

--- a/src/dynapi.c
+++ b/src/dynapi.c
@@ -2685,7 +2685,7 @@
   { "rect_width",	"BD", sizeof (BITCODE_BD),  OFF (struct _dwg_entity_MTEXT, rect_width),
-    0,0,0, 40 },
+    0,0,0, 41 },
   { "text_height",	"BD", sizeof (BITCODE_BD),  OFF (struct _dwg_entity_MTEXT, text_height),
     0,0,0, 40 },
